body:
This is a note of how to change Tab key behavior in Textarea.

Normally, if you use Tab key inside Textarea, the following input element will be focused. To do so, receive keydown events and insert `\t` in the specified position.

## Actual code

### app.html.html

```html
<form [formGroup]="form" class="form-control">
	<textarea
		#mdInput
		formControlName="markdown"
		(keydown)="handleKeyDown($event, mdInput)"
	></textarea>
</form>
```

### app.ts.ts

```ts
export class AppComponent {
	form = new FormGroup({
		markdown: new FormControl('')
	})

	handleKeyDown(event: KeyboardEvent, mdInput: HTMLTextAreaElement) {
		if (event.key === 'Tab') {
			/** Tabキー押下時のフォーカス遷移をなくす */
			event.preventDefault();
			/** HTMLTextAreaElementから現在のカーソル位置を取得 */
			const defaultLocation = mdInput.selectionStart;
			const left = this.form.controls.markdown.value.slice(0, mdInput.selectionStart);
			const right = this.form.controls.markdown.value.slice(mdInput.selectionStart);
			this.form.controls.markdown.setValue(left + '\t' + right);
			/** テキストエリア内のカーソルをtabの後に移動 */
			mdInput.selectionEnd = defaultLocation + 1;
		}
	}
}
```

### app.sc.scss

The display width of `\t` can be managed by the following 。s.

```scss
#mdInput  {
	tab-size: 2;
}
```

